Manager, Loan Originations 


Submit Resumé





                  Are you interested in joining a startup and helping it reach the next stage of growth? Are you a proven real estate professional with a successful track record of lending, particularly in the private money arena for commercial loans on residential real estate?
                

                  GROUNDFLOOR is an Atlanta­based fintech startup opening the market for peer­to-peer lending in real estate. We're expanding our Lending Operations team, responsible for scaling best practices and efficiencies to create the best possible customer experience for our borrowers.
                
What You'll Do

Become an expert at using lead generation tools to routinely extract contacts and create accurate and targeted lists of prospects.
Conduct sales development best practices with email, phone, and social drips to connect with new prospects.
Manage the collection and organization of all elements of the loan package and coordinate submission to Loan Committee.
Find, administer, help develop and optimize the tools and services utilized by GROUNDFLOOR's sales and operations organizations as we begin to scale nationally.


What You'll Need

Bachelor's degree
Strong written communication, phone, presentation, and interpersonal skills.
Hustle and persistence
Must be comfortable and effective with top of the funnel objections, prospecting, cold calling, online, as well as have excellent interpersonal & technical skills.
Highly organized and strong time management skills.
Contagious passion and empathy for the customer, but the tenacity to get them through the sales funnel efficiently.
Experience collaborating and planning with tools such as Salesforce, Desk.com, Slack and the like.
While we are not a traditional real estate lender, experience with residential real estate is highly desired.
Experience working on a fast­ paced, highly ­visible team; your work will have serious impact here.
Balance attention to detail with swift execution  we need to do things quickly, and we need to do them well.
Balancing those can be challenging, and this should be a strength.
Experience with standard residential real estate laws and real estate loan closings will be a significant advantage.
Desire to grow and learn new things every day.
Ability to work in fast paced, changing environment with minimal direction.


Bottom Line
You have to be ready to hustle! We move fast...done is better than perfect, and continual iteration is important. You must be ready and excited to learn on your feet and help build a growing business. This position is based in Atlanta.


                    GROUNDFLOOR Finance, Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer and does not discriminate against any employee or applicant for employment because of race, color, sex, age, national origin, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, status as a veteran, and basis of disability or any other federal, state or local protected class.





Director, Lending Operations 


Submit Resumé





                  Are you interested in joining a startup and helping it reach the next stage of growth? Are you a proven real estate professional with a successful track record of lending, particularly in the private money arena for commercial loans on residential real estate?
                

                  GROUNDFLOOR is an Atlanta­based fintech startup opening the market for peer­to-peer lending in real estate. We're expanding our Lending Operations team, responsible for scaling best practices and efficiencies to create the best possible customer experience for our borrowers.
                
What You'll Do

Serve as an in­house lending expert, helping to refine our lending policy and practices.
Manage the process for underwriting loans, servicing loans and making sure our lenders are well informed and repaid.
Manage all policy related to portfolio risk management.
Manage the collection and organization of all elements of the loan package and coordinate submission to the SEC.
Lead our Loan Committee.
Find, administer, help develop and optimize the tools and services utilized by GROUNDFLOOR's operations organization as we begin to scale nationally.
Help drive the evolution of our proprietary underwriting algorithm.

What You'll Need

Bachelor's degree.
Contagious passion and empathy for the customer, but the tenacity to ensure that we have a transparent, robust and appropriate lending policy.
Experience collaborating and planning with tools such as Atlassian's JIRA and Confluence, Desk.com, Hubspot and the like is a plus.
While we are not a hard money lender; experience as a hard money lender is highly desirable.
An opinion on traditional lending policies found in the market—what's good, what's bad and how/where technology might be able to improve and influence our lending policy in order to create the best possible experience for our borrowers.
Experience working on a fast­paced, highly­visible team; your work will have serious impact here.
Balance attention to detail with swift execution ­ we need to do things quickly, and we need to do them well. Balancing those can be challenging, and this should be a strength.
Experience with standard residential real estate laws and real estate loan closings will be a significant advantage.
Desire to grow and learn new things every day.

Bottom Line
You have to be ready to hustle! We move fast...done is better than perfect, and continual iteration is important. You must be ready and excited to learn on your feet and help build a growing business.


                    GROUNDFLOOR Finance,  Inc. is an  Equal Opportunity Employer  and does  not discriminate  against any employee  or  applicant for employment  because of  race, color, sex, age,  national  origin, religion, sexual  orientation,  gender  identity  and/or  expression, status  as  a veteran,  and basis of  disability  or  any other federal,  state or  local protected class.
                  





Regional Director, Multiple Locations 


Submit Resumé




About GROUNDFLOOR

                  GROUNDFLOOR is an Atlanta-based fintech startup opening the market for peer-to-peer lending in real estate. The ideal candidate is motivated by the opportunity to build a distinctive brand, product and service that stands apart in a field of many that aim to reformat banking, finance and investing. As a company, we value and select for intellect, strategic thinking, authenticity and integrity. 
                
Job Description

                  The Regional Director is a critical role that will lead the company's growth and development in certain key geographic markets.  
                

                  Your primary focus will initially be loan (and borrower) acquisition and relationship management. However, as the lead for this new market, this will be one of the most demanding jobs that GROUNDFLOOR has to offer. It will require a unique blend of talent, guts, leadership and creativity. You'll need to have--or quickly develop--a deep understanding of the commercial loan market for residential real estate in your market.   
                
What You'll Do

Develop a loan pipeline.
Help refine our target customer, how to best reach them and determine how they want to be sold to.
Analyze loan and borrower data to find trends, and untapped opportunities.
Provide a closed customer feedback loop that helps shape product and business strategy.
Assist the marketing team in variety of local marketing campaigns and activity.
You will immerse yourself in the local real estate market including, for example, meetups and forums in order to rapidly grow brand awareness and customer adoption for both borrowers and lenders.
Help establish a predictable, repeatable funnel and playbook to scale our other cities through developing and sharing best practices.
Identify strategic partnerships and alliances in your local market.

What You'll Need

Bachelor's degree.
7+ Years sales, product and/or marketing experience.
Experience working with or as any or all of the following: hard money lenders, residential GC's, residential real estate investors, residential real estate lenders, residential real estate brokers.
Excellent communication and relational skills.
Data-driven decision mentality and sound business judgment through strong analytical thinking.
Deep local knowledge of the Atlanta residential real estate market (or ability to develop quickly).
Creative solutions driven mindset, with a get it done attitude.
Killer networking skills with ability to make smart partnerships happen.
Entrepreneurial DNA, hunter mindset and the fearlessness of a honey badger.
Experience opening a new market.
Product Marketing.
Intermediate Microsoft and Google for Work tools including MS Excel (pivot tables, vlookups, etc.), MS Powerpoint, MS Word, Google Sheets, Google Docs and Google Slides.
The candidate ideally has a deep "rolodex" (especially in the real estate industry). Otherwise, they'll need to be a rockstar networker!



                    GROUNDFLOOR Finance, Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer and does not discriminate against any employee or applicant for employment because of race, color, sex, age, national origin, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, status as a veteran, and basis of disability or any other federal, state or local protected class.
                  





Underwriting Manager


Submit Resumé




Are you interested in joining a startup and helping it reach the next stage of growth? Are you a proven real estate professional with a successful track record of underwriting commercial loans on residential real estate for new construction and fix & flips?
GROUNDFLOOR is looking to establish its underwriting team that is responsible for scaling best practices and efficiencies to help ensure that we are lending to the right people on the right projects.
What You'll Do

Underwrite commercial loans on residential real estate.
Help manage all policy related to portfolio risk management and risk mitigation for the entire loan life cycle (including originations, closings and draw administration).
Develop best practices and process for underwriting and risk management throughout the loan life cycle.
Ensure that all loans are underwritten according to our disclosures with the SEC as well as GROUNDFLOOR lenders.
Participate in and help structure our Loan Committee, particularly as we scale and expand nationally.
Find, administer, help develop and optimize the tools and services utilized by GROUNDFLOOR's Lending Operations as they relate to underwriting and risk management.

What You'll Need

Bachelor's degree.
Experience underwriting commercial loans on residential real estate.
Experience with (or as) a general contractor, particularly experience estimating budgets for fix & flips and new construction of single-family residential properties in multiple geographies.
Experience with standard industry tools such as MLS, etc.
Contagious passion and empathy for the customer, but the tenacity to help ensure that we have a transparent, robust and appropriate lending policy.
While we are not a hard money lender, experience as a hard money lender is highly desirable.
An opinion on traditional lending and underwriting policies found in the market—what's good, what's bad and how/where technology might be able to improve and influence our lending policy in order to create the best possible experience for our borrowers.
Experience collaborating and planning with tools such as Atlassian's JIRA and Confluence, Desk.com, Hubspot and the like is a plus.
Experience working on a fast-paced, highly-visible team; your work will have serious impact here.
Balance attention to detail with swift execution - we need to do things quickly, and we need to do them well. Balancing those can be challenging, and this should be a strength.
Desire to grow and learn new things every day.

Bottom Line
You have to be ready to hustle! We move fast...done is better than perfect, and continual iteration is important. You must be ready and excited to learn on your feet and help build a growing business.


                    GROUNDFLOOR Finance, Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer and does not discriminate against any employee or applicant for employment because of race, color, sex, age, national origin, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, status as a veteran, and basis of disability or any other federal, state or local protected class.
                  


















