Patrick Donoghue has served as Director of Lending Operations for Groundfloor since January 2016. Prior to this Patrick served as Senior Associate for RevitaLending where he worked to optimize the firm’s capital market structure and proliferate the loan growth model. As VP of Wholesale Operations for ACC Mortgage Patrick managed the entire loan process for a significant broker channel reviewing and funding private money loan transactions.
Patrick has been active in the private lending space since 2006 underwriting, originating and servicing private money loans. Prior to this Patrick served as production manager and originator for various mortgage companies and began his career as a Branch Manager for the United States Senate FCU. As Director of Lending Operations Patrick is helping refine Groundfloor’s lending policy and practices. Heading the underwriting of all loans and managing the real estate closing process.
Patrick graduated from Edinboro University of Pennsylvania with a B.A. in Psychology in 1997













