David Morken
Board Observer




David Morken is the Co-founder and CEO of Bandwidth, one of the nation's largest and fastest-growing communications technology companies. Founded in 1999, and a certified CLEC in 49 states, Bandwidth is disrupting the telecom industry with its customer-first focus and software development horsepower. Bandwidth operates both business and consumer divisions, serving corporate clients as diverse as Google and Skype, as well as consumers everywhere who want to save money on their smartphone bills. David has led Bandwidth through tremendous growth since its inception including, most recently, the launch of Republic Wireless.  As the nation's first hybrid calling mobile operator, Republic Wireless leverages the disruptive power of Wi-Fi to provide members with unlimited voice, text and data service.
Prior to founding Bandwidth, David was called to active duty by the Marine Corps in 1995 and served four years as a Judge Advocate, criminal prosecutor and headquarters company commander. David is a graduate of the University of Notre Dame Law School and a member of the Virginia Bar Association. He received his undergraduate degree from Oral Roberts University.












Microsoft personalized ad preferences




 













To opt out of personalized ads in this browser, your browser history must allow first-party and third-party cookies and you must have your browsing experience set to NOT delete browsing history on exit. Instructions for enabling cookies and configuring your browsing history may be available in your browsers settings, privacy, or help documentation.

















