Co-Founder and Principal, Hyde Street Holdings, LLC. (“HSH”), est. 1996.
HSH concentrates on strategic, operational and financial opportunities created by under optimized circumstances or new ventures. Prior to HSH, Mr. Healy was Co-Founder and CEO of Hanford/Healy Companies (1988-1996), which sold to GMAC Commercial Mortgage.
{"Board Memberships include"=>"AvalonBay Communities (REIT) NYSE (AVB) 1996-Present; Prologis Targeted U.S. Logistics Fund (Independent Council) 2004-2013 (Subsidiary of NYSE company Prologis) and Libritas 2000-2002, Sold 12-03 to Next Web, Inc."}
John holds the CRE and MAI (Life Non-Practicing) designations, and is a fellow Royal Institution of Chartered Surveyors (FRICS). He also is on the board of Research Triangle Chapter’s NACD (President 2006-2009); Trustee of ULI, 2009-Present; serving on the ULI Foundation Board 2011-Present and Chair of the Audit Committee 2013-Present and various other non-profits in the community.
